    "The initial density, number of molecules, temperature and time step were consistent with Zeng et al.",
    "Snapshots and properties were recorded every 0.1 ps (1,000 time steps).",
    "ANI-1xnr was trained to reference calculations computed with BLYP functional and TZV2P basis set, whereas Zeng et al.",
    "utilized the MN15 functional and 6-31G** basis set 24.",
    "Since reaction rates are extremely sensitive to energy barriers, this difference in the DFT functional and basis set can lead to a substantial difference in overall reaction rates."
